    <name>
      <text>Determine which ones of statements are tautologies (Morara)</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="html">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>Determine which of the following statements are tautologies (i.e. are true regardless of the truth values of \(p, q\) and \(r\)).<br />Hint: You could create a truth table to find out. <br />[[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]</p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="html">
      <text><![CDATA[<p style="text-align: left;" dir="ltr">These are the truth tables for the 3 formulas:</p>
<p style="text-align: left;" dir="ltr"><span style="font-size: 0.9375rem;">{@truth_table(choices[1][1])@}</span></p>
<p style="text-align: left;" dir="ltr"> </p>
<p dir="ltr"><span style="font-size: 0.9375rem;">{@truth_table(choices[2][1])@}</span></p>
<p dir="ltr"><span style="font-size: 0.9375rem;">{@truth_table(choices[3][1])@}</span></p>
<p dir="ltr">So we see that the expressions that are tautologies are {@mcq_correct(choices)@}</p>
<p> </p>]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
    <defaultgrade>1</defaultgrade>
